The core problem
                                                                                                                                                          
  You can't drain 15 nodes simply by cordoning them — the pods on those nodes need somewhere to land. Right now, schedulable capacity is artificially
  constrained by inflated requests. Fix requests first, then drain.                                                                                       
                                                        
  ---                                                                                                                                                     
  Phase 1 — Free schedulable capacity (do this first)   
                                                                                                                                                          
  Right-size the most egregiously over-provisioned pods. These changes are low-risk because the pods are barely using anything.
                                                                                                                                                          
  Priority targets:                                                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                          
  ┌────────────────────┬───────────────┬─────────────────┬───────────────────┬────────────┐                                                               
  │     Namespace      │      Pod      │ Current request │ Suggested request │ Mem freed  │
  ├────────────────────┼───────────────┼─────────────────┼───────────────────┼────────────┤                                                               
  │ vm-aisecops        │ vmstorage x4  │ 2000m / 16Gi    │ 100m / 1Gi        │ ~60Gi      │
  ├────────────────────┼───────────────┼─────────────────┼───────────────────┼────────────┤                                                               
  │ vm-ocr             │ vmstorage x2  │ 2000m / 16Gi    │ 100m / 1Gi        │ ~30Gi      │                                                               
  ├────────────────────┼───────────────┼─────────────────┼───────────────────┼────────────┤                                                               
  │ vm-k8s             │ vmstorage x16 │ 8000m / —       │ 500m / —          │ ~124 cores │                                                               
  ├────────────────────┼───────────────┼─────────────────┼───────────────────┼────────────┤                                                               
  │ vm-dp              │ vmselect x14  │ 1000m / 2Gi     │ 50m / 768Mi       │ ~18Gi      │
  ├────────────────────┼───────────────┼─────────────────┼───────────────────┼────────────┤                                                               
  │ vm-cloudconfigsync │ vmselect x3   │ 1000m / 2Gi     │ 50m / 768Mi       │ ~4Gi       │
  └────────────────────┴───────────────┴─────────────────┴───────────────────┴────────────┘                                                               
                                                       
  This alone frees ~110Gi of schedulable memory and ~130 CPU cores — enough headroom for pods from 4-6 more nodes to bin-pack onto existing nodes.        
                                                       
