  ---                                                                                                                                                     
  Phase 3 — Drain sequence per node                                                                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                          
  For each node in the batch:                                                                                                                             
  # 1. Cordon — stop new pods scheduling here                                                                                                             
  kubectl cordon <node>                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                          
  # 2. Check what's running on it                                                                                                                         
  kubectl get pods --all-namespaces --field-selector spec.nodeName=<node>                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                          
  # 3. Drain — evicts all pods (respects PodDisruptionBudgets)                                                                                            
  kubectl drain <node> --ignore-daemonsets --delete-emptydir-data --grace-period=60                                                                       
                                                                                                                                                          
  # 4. Verify pods rescheduled healthy before removing from node group                                                                                    
  kubectl get pods --all-namespaces | grep -E "Pending|CrashLoop"                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                          
  # 5. Remove from AWS node group (via eksctl, AWS console, or autoscaler)                                                                                
                                                                                  
